15:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both Aevo and RabbitX use hourly funding rate calculations based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. Aevo's custom rollup enables faster rate updates but may show higher volatility due to lower liquidity. RabbitX leverages Starknet's infrastructure for rate calculations, potentially offering more stable rates as it scales. Both platforms use off-chain order matching with on-chain settlement, affecting funding rate precision. The lack of gas fees on RabbitX may lead to more frequent arbitrage activity, keeping funding rates closer to theoretical values."}]]}]
16:["$","$L17",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which platform offers better funding rate opportunities?","answer":"Aevo typically shows higher funding rate volatility due to lower liquidity, creating more arbitrage opportunities. RabbitX's zero gas fees make it more cost-effective for frequent funding rate strategies despite potentially tighter spreads."},{"question":"How do settlement mechanisms affect funding rates?","answer":"Aevo's custom rollup allows for faster settlement and rate updates but introduces rollup risk. RabbitX uses established Starknet infrastructure, offering better decentralization but potentially slower rate adjustments during high volatility."},{"question":"Which exchange has better liquidity for funding arbitrage?","answer":"Both platforms have limited liquidity compared to major CEXs. Aevo's multi-product approach may fragment liquidity, while RabbitX's focused perpetuals offering concentrates available liquidity in fewer markets."},{"question":"Are there gas cost differences for funding payments?","answer":"RabbitX eliminates gas fees entirely, making it more profitable for funding rate strategies. Aevo requires gas payments on its rollup, though costs are significantly lower than Ethereum mainnet transactions."}]}]
